						<summary>

						<p>Kadambavanēśvara temple, central shrine, south wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Madiraikoṇḍa Parakēsarivarman (Parāntaka I) Year 26.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the gift of 90 sheep to God Śiṟuttirukkōyil-pperumānaḍigaḷ in Uṟumūr, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadānam</hi> in Vaḍakarai-nal-vayalūr-kūṟṟam by Kōvaḍi Nīli, wife <hi rend="italic">(maṇavāṭṭi)</hi> of <hi rend="italic">manṟāḍi</hi> Nakkaṉ Tūṅkānai of Koṟṟamaṅgalam and the undertaking by the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Uṟumūr who took over the sheep to burn a perpetual lamp with an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee daily.</p>						

						</summary>
